comment: <blockquote><ul><li>Added <code>hasnt_table()</code>, <code>hasnt_view()</code>, and <code>hasnt_column()</code>.</li><li>Added <code>hasnt_pk()</code>, <code>hasnt_fk()</code></li><li>[â€¦]</li></ul></blockquote><p>Those are grammatically awful in English. It helps, when naming a function, to use good grammar. Otherwise, the function won't be connected well with what the person tries to do, and thus won't be remembered properly.</code><p>Possible improvements (instead of <code>hasnt_foo(bar)â</code>):</p><ul><li><code>has_no_foo(bar)</code></li><li><code>doesnt_have_foo(bar)</code></li><li><code>not_has_foo(bar)</code></li></ul><p>It's unfortunate that the English grammar of â€œhas fooâ€/â€œdoesn't have fooâ€ isn't a nice fit to function names; but choosing poor names will just make your API harder to use.</p>
